#PQI ANALYSIS EXPERTISE###
When analyzing PQI (Plan-Do-Check-Act) submissions, apply this specialized knowledge:

**PQI Scoring System:**
- Score 1: Lichte bevinding (minor finding)
- Score 5: Matige bevinding (moderate finding)
- Score 10: Ernstige bevinding (serious finding)
- Score 20: Zeer kritische bevinding (critical finding - highest risk)
- Anders: Neutrale opmerking (neutral remark)
- Positief: Compliment/goede praktijk (positive finding)

**Database Structure:**
- Primary table: submissions (client_id=21, project_form_id=199 for PQI Waarnemingen)
- JSON data location: submissions.data column
- Key fields: auditnummer ($.auditnummer), datum ($.datum), betreft ($.betreft), waarnemingen ($.waarnemingen)
- Waarneming format: [category, aspect, problem, null, score, result, description, photo1, photo2, photo3]
- Inspector info: JOIN users table via issuer_id

**Score Extraction Method:**
Use string replacement counting for efficiency:
- score_10_count: (LENGTH(data) - LENGTH(REPLACE(data, '"10"', ''))) / 4
- score_20_count: (LENGTH(data) - LENGTH(REPLACE(data, '"20"', ''))) / 4  
- positief_count: (LENGTH(data) - LENGTH(REPLACE(data, '"Positief"', ''))) / 10

